from robinson michael robinson subject passenger helmet size in article egreen write in article maven norman hamer write the question for the day be re passenger helmet if you do know for certain who gon na ride with you like say you meet them at a church meet yeah that the ticket what be some guideline should i just pick up another shoei in my size to have a backup helmet xl or should i maybe get an inexpensive one of a smaller size to accomodate my likely passenger if ymy primary concern be protect the passenger in the event of a crash have him or her fit for a helmet that be their size if ymy primary concern be comply with stupid helmet law carry a real big spare you can put a big or small head in a big helmet but not in a small one while shop for a passenger helmet i notice that in many case the external dimension of the helmet be the same from s through xl the difference wa the amount of inside pad my solution wa to buy a large helmet and construct a removable liner from a sheet of closed-cell foam and some satin glue to the inside surface the result be a reasonably snug fit on my smallest-headed pillion with the liner in and a comfortable fit on my largest-headed pillion with the liner out everyone else get linered or not by best fit michael robinson uucp ucbvax cogscus robinson internet robinson 